  <rte>
    <name>The Crinkle Crags from Great Langdale</name>
    <desc>Despite its obvious popularity this remains one of Lakeland's great walks. Sufficiently challenging yet not too arduous it provides walkers with great scenery supplemented with that unique mountain "feel".</desc>
    <author>Copyright Walking Britain</author>
	<url>www.walkingbritain.co.uk/walk-1132-description</url>
